The first line of defense that can be used to reduce the risk of infection is through the use of facial masks, both surgical masks and respiratory masks N95 (series number 1860s) to help control the spread of the virus.
The surgical mask ensures that the splash of a potentially infected person does not follow the air or stick to the surface of the material, where the splash can be passed on to others.
